# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Docker build context excludes — repo-root context (monorepo).
# Applied to both apps/fanaa/Dockerfile and services/api/Dockerfile builds.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Per-workspace install trees — pnpm regenerates these inside the image.
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build outputs — Next.js regenerates these inside the image.
.next
**/.next
out
.vercel
.turbo
**/.turbo

# Local env files — only .env.example variants are allowed in.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!**/.env.example
!**/.env.admin.example

# VCS + IDE noise.
#
# Note on the build SHA: an earlier iteration of the Studio Dockerfile
# tried to read .git/HEAD inside the build to derive the SHA. EasyPanel
# does not ship .git/ in its build context — it downloads a GitHub
# archive ZIP and builds from that — so the .git approach failed at
# `COPY .git`. The current Dockerfile uses EasyPanel's auto-injected
# `GIT_SHA` build arg instead, which sidesteps the build-context issue
# entirely. There is no need to re-include any .git metadata here.
.git
.gitignore
.idea
.vscode
.cursor

# Logs + caches.
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.DS_Store
.cache
coverage
playwright-report
test-results

# Documentation — keep PLATFORM.md out of the image but allow README.md.
*.md
!README.md

# Cross-workspace exclusions —
# The fanaa Docker build doesn't need services/ (the FastAPI tree),
# and the services/api build doesn't see apps/ because its build context
# is scoped to ./services/api by docker-compose.
services
